# Next.js Dashboard Rules

## Framework
- Next.js 15.2 with App Router
- React 19 with Server Components by default
- TypeScript strict mode
- Tailwind CSS 4.0 for styling

## Routing
- File-based routing in src/app/
- Use layout.tsx for shared layouts
- Use loading.tsx for loading states
- Use error.tsx for error boundaries
- Prefer Server Components; add "use client" only when needed

## Data Fetching
- Server Components fetch data directly (no useEffect)
- Server Actions for mutations
- Revalidate with revalidatePath/revalidateTag
- Gateway API base URL from NEXT_PUBLIC_GATEWAY_URL env var

## Styling
- Tailwind utility classes only (no CSS modules, no styled-components)
- Use cn() helper (clsx + tailwind-merge) for conditional classes
- Design tokens via Tailwind config

## TypeScript
- Strict mode enabled
- Explicit return types on exported functions
- Use interface for object shapes, type for unions/intersections
- No any — use unknown for truly unknown types
